cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

The paper proposes a method for text categorization, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The method also involves computing term weights and storing them in a knowledgebase, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques such as logistic regression (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of Btree indexing data structure implies the involvement of database systems (cs.DB).
